FBIS3-53624 "drnes011_s_94026" FBIS-NES-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 Iran Ahmad Khomeyni Receives Islamic Revolution Guards LD1601213894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 2030 GMT 16 Jan 94 LD1601213894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] On the auspicious birthday of Aba Abdullah al-Husayn, peace be upon him, and the Guards Day, Hojjat ol-Eslam val-Moslemin Seyyed Ahmad Khomeyni met a group of Islamic revolution guards today. Referring to the great role played by Imam Husayn in revival of the genuine Islam, he said: Imam Husayn, peace be upon him, by creating the epic of 'Ashura, changed the course of Islam's history for ever to serve the interests of justice-seeking free people. While offering congratulations to all the Islamic revolution guards on the Guards Day, he added: Our armed forces, by giving up their lives and assets, brought honor and pride to Islam and the country. [passage omitted] He went on: An important Islamic and national duty today is to assist and encourage the government, to create hope, and to give assurance to people and officials.
